text: Annika Nordenskjöld Olsén (1 December 1975 - 3 September 2014), better known by her stage name Niki Nordenskjöld, was a Swedish actress and illustrator. She was best known for her role as Lina in the television comedy series Solsidan. Nordenskjöld was born in Gothenburg. She started her career in 1990 at the age of 15. Nordenskjöld died from cancer on 3 September 2014 in Stockholm, aged 38. ==References== ==Other websites== * * Niki Nordenskjöld at The Swedish Film Database Category:1975 births Category:2014 deaths Category:Cancer deaths in Sweden Category:Actors from Gothenburg Category:Swedish artists Category:Swedish movie actors Category:Swedish stage actors Category:Swedish television actors Category:20th-century artists Category:21st-century artists
